<title>UK: Ascot says Suter bid unconditional.</title>
<headline>Ascot says Suter bid unconditional.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-08-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Ascot Holding Plc's 290 million stg offer for Suter Plc was declared unconditional, after approval from a large majority of shareholders and warrant holders.</p>
<p>Ascot said in a statement it had received acceptances for shares representing 81.6 percent of the company.</p>
<p>Ascot made the offer, which valued each Suter share at about 237 pence, on July 25.</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7717</p>
